parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle cam can cause unintended acceleration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: the throttle cabling mechanism sticks in the partially "open" position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel line can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, or engine compartment fires.
symptoms: fuel spraying onto the exhaust system
fuel line failure at the point where the fuel line goes through rubber isolation/mounting blocks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the vehicle to vibrate, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: smoke coming from the front left wheel.

The failure of dealerships to properly repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks for drivers and passengers, as well as frustration and inconvenience for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships cancel or postpone repair appointments due to billing or reimbursement issues
leaving recalled vehicles unrepaired and potentially unsafe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor communication between manufacturers and dealerships can lead to delays or failures in recall repairs, putting vehicle owners at risk and causing frustration.
symptoms: Dealerships lack proper billing codes or reimbursement information
leading to cancelled or postponed repair appointments
and vehicle owners are left to navigate the repair process.
